  "title": "Management of chyle leaks",
  "abstract": "The formation of the chylous fistula is a potentially serious complication of surgery in the neck. This is especially true of the left side of the neck, where 75% of cases occur. Overall, the reported incidence following surgery to the neck is of the order of 1 to 2.5% of cases. Exactly when this situation, if it arises, should be managed is controversial. This paper is a review of the current literature and recommends current best practice. The basic science of chyle, the important decisions of clinical management regarding conservative “watch and wait” versus surgical intervention, the timing of such surgical interventions, and the aggressiveness of these interventions are discussed.",
